---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="gl1tch — your AI, your terminal, your rules">

<main>

<!-- ── Hero ──────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="hero" id="hero">
<div class="hero-wrap">
  <div class="hero-left">
    <h1 class="hero-title">gl1tch</h1>
    <p class="hero-tagline">Shell does the work.<br>LLM does the thinking.<br>You own the workflow.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <pre class="code copyable hero-cmd" data-copy="brew install 8op-org/tap/glitch"><span class="p">$</span> brew install 8op-org/tap/glitch</pre>
      <div class="hero-links">
        <a href="https://github.com/8op-org/gl1tch" class="btn btn-primary">GitHub</a>
        <a href="/docs/getting-started" class="btn btn-ghost">Docs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-right">
    <pre class="code hero-demo"><span class="r">;; this is a workflow</span>

(<span class="k">workflow</span> <span class="s">"pr-review"</span>

  (<span class="k">step</span> <span class="s">"fetch"</span>
    (<span class="k">run</span> <span class="s">"gh pr view {'{{.input}}'} --json title,body"</span>))

  (<span class="k">step</span> <span class="s">"diff"</span>
    (<span class="k">run</span> <span class="s">"gh pr diff {'{{.input}}'}"</span>))

  (<span class="k">step</span> <span class="s">"review"</span>
    (<span class="k">llm</span>
      <span class="r">:prompt</span> <span class="s">```
        PR: {'{{step "fetch"}}'}
        Diff: {'{{step "diff"}}'}
        Review as a senior engineer.
        ```</span>)))</pre>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- ── What it does ─────────────────────────── -->
<section id="features">
<div class="wrap-wide">
  <div class="section-label">what you get</div>

  <div class="features-grid">

    <div class="feature-card feature-hero-card">
      <div class="feature-number">01</div>
      <h3>S-expressions, not YAML</h3>
      <p>Workflows are parenthesized lists. Every construct composes — retry wraps timeout wraps step. No indentation wars. No anchor hacks.</p>
      <pre class="code feature-code">(<span class="k">retry</span> <span class="s">2</span>
  (<span class="k">timeout</span> <span class="s">"30s"</span>
    (<span class="k">step</span> <span class="s">"fetch"</span>
      (<span class="k">run</span> <span class="s">"curl -sf ..."</span>))))</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-number">02</div>
      <h3>Phase gates</h3>
      <p>Verification built into the language. Gates must pass before the phase completes. If they fail, the phase retries.</p>
      <pre class="code feature-code">(<span class="k">phase</span> <span class="s">"verify"</span> <span class="r">:retries</span> <span class="s">1</span>
  (<span class="k">gate</span> <span class="s">"check"</span>
    (<span class="k">run</span> <span class="s">"python3 verify.py"</span>)))</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-number">03</div>
      <h3>Tiered escalation</h3>
      <p>Start on your local model for free. gl1tch self-evaluates the output. Escalates to cloud only when quality demands it.</p>
      <pre class="code feature-code"><span class="r">;; tier 0: lm-studio (free)</span>
<span class="r">;; tier 1: copilot</span>
<span class="r">;; tier 2: claude</span>
(<span class="k">llm</span> <span class="r">:tier</span> <span class="s">0</span> <span class="r">:format</span> <span class="s">"json"</span> <span class="r">:prompt</span> <span class="s">"..."</span>)</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-number">04</div>
      <h3>Plugins are directories</h3>
      <p>A plugin is a folder of <code>.glitch</code> files. Each file is a subcommand. Args become flags. No compilation. No release pipeline.</p>
      <pre class="code feature-code"><span class="p">$</span> glitch plugin github prs --since week
<span class="r">["Fix flaky test", "Add retry logic"]</span></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-number">05</div>
      <h3>Knowledge index</h3>
      <p><code>glitch index</code> ingests your repos into Elasticsearch. <code>glitch observe</code> queries them in natural language. Workflows use it as memory.</p>
      <pre class="code feature-code"><span class="p">$</span> glitch observe "PRs that failed CI this week"</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-number">06</div>
      <h3>Built-in A/B testing</h3>
      <p>Run the same prompt through different models or strategies. A neutral judge scores each branch. One form, automatic winner selection.</p>
      <pre class="code feature-code">(<span class="k">compare</span>
  (<span class="k">branch</span> <span class="s">"local"</span>
    (<span class="k">llm</span> <span class="r">:model</span> <span class="s">"qwen2.5:7b"</span> <span class="r">:prompt</span> <span class="s">"..."</span>))
  (<span class="k">branch</span> <span class="s">"cloud"</span>
    (<span class="k">llm</span> <span class="r">:model</span> <span class="s">"claude"</span> <span class="r">:prompt</span> <span class="s">"..."</span>))
  (<span class="k">review</span> <span class="r">:criteria</span> (<span class="s">"accuracy"</span> <span class="s">"clarity"</span>)))</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-number">07</div>
      <h3>Composable transforms</h3>
      <p>Thread data through steps, filter collections, fold results. Lisp-inspired forms that compose without glue scripts.</p>
      <pre class="code feature-code">(<span class="k">-></span> <span class="s">"raw-data"</span>
  (<span class="k">filter</span> <span class="s">"jq '.severity > 3'"</span>)
  (<span class="k">reduce</span> <span class="s">"summarize"</span>
    (<span class="k">llm</span> <span class="r">:prompt</span> <span class="s">"..."</span>)))</pre>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- ── The workflow ─────────────────────────── -->
<section id="how">
<div class="wrap-wide">
  <div class="section-label">how it works</div>
  <h2>Write a workflow. Or let AI write it for you.</h2>

  <div class="how-grid">
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="how-num">01 shell gathers context</div>
      <pre class="code">(<span class="k">step</span> <span class="s">"examples"</span>
  (<span class="k">run</span> <span class="s">"cat examples/*.glitch"</span>))
(<span class="k">step</span> <span class="s">"structure"</span>
  (<span class="k">run</span> <span class="s">"find internal/ cmd/ -name '*.go'"</span>))</pre>
      <p>Shell steps gather your repo context — code, docs, git history. Free and deterministic.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="how-num">02 LLM generates or reasons</div>
      <pre class="code">(<span class="k">step</span> <span class="s">"generate"</span>
  (<span class="k">llm</span> <span class="r">:tier</span> <span class="s">0</span>
    <span class="r">:prompt</span> <span class="s">"Write docs using:
    {'{{step \"examples\"}}'}..."</span>))</pre>
      <p>Tiered routing tries local LLM first. Escalates to cloud only if quality demands it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="how-num">03 gates verify before shipping</div>
      <pre class="code">(<span class="k">phase</span> <span class="s">"verify"</span> <span class="r">:retries</span> <span class="s">1</span>
  (<span class="k">gate</span> <span class="s">"no-hallucinations"</span>
    (<span class="k">run</span> <span class="s">"python3 scripts/gate.py"</span>)))</pre>
      <p>Shell-based gates catch hallucinated features, leaked internals, and missing coverage. Retries on failure.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="how-num">04 compare and pick the best</div>
      <pre class="code">(<span class="k">compare</span>
  (<span class="k">branch</span> <span class="s">"local"</span>
    (<span class="k">llm</span> <span class="r">:model</span> <span class="s">"qwen2.5:7b"</span> <span class="r">:prompt</span> <span class="s">"..."</span>))
  (<span class="k">branch</span> <span class="s">"cloud"</span>
    (<span class="k">llm</span> <span class="r">:provider</span> <span class="s">"claude"</span> <span class="r">:prompt</span> <span class="s">"..."</span>))
  (<span class="k">review</span> <span class="r">:criteria</span> (<span class="s">"accuracy"</span> <span class="s">"depth"</span>)))</pre>
      <p>Run branches in parallel, let a neutral judge score them. Pick the winner automatically — or review the comparison yourself.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- ── This site builds itself ─────────────── -->
<section id="meta">
<div class="wrap">
  <div class="section-label">proof it works</div>
  <h2>This site builds itself.</h2>
  <p class="section-copy">Every page was created by a gl1tch workflow. AI writes the content from real repo context. Shell gates verify no hallucinations before anything ships.</p>

  <pre class="code meta-trace"><span class="p">$</span> glitch workflow run site-create-page --set topic="batch comparison runs"

<span class="term-header">&gt;&gt; site-create-page</span>
  <span class="term-dim">&gt;</span> <span class="term-dim">existing-docs</span>
  <span class="term-dim">&gt;</span> <span class="term-dim">examples</span>
  <span class="term-dim">&gt;</span> <span class="term-dim">repo-structure</span>
  <span class="term-dim">&gt;</span> <span class="term-dim">existing-pages</span>
  <span class="term-llm">&gt;</span> <span class="term-llm">generate</span>               <span class="term-anno">lm-studio</span>
    <span class="term-anno">tier 0: lm-studio accepted</span>
  <span class="term-llm">&check;</span> <span class="term-llm">generate</span>               <span class="term-anno">3965 tok &middot; 52.6s</span>
  <span class="term-dim">&gt;</span> <span class="term-dim">save-stub</span>
  <span class="term-dim">&gt;</span> <span class="term-dim">rebuild-json</span>

<span class="term-header">&gt;&gt;&gt; Phase "content-verify"</span>
  <span class="term-pass">&check;</span> <span class="term-gate">gate no-hallucinations</span>  <span class="term-pass">PASS</span>
  <span class="term-pass">&check;</span> <span class="term-gate">gate stub-coverage</span>      <span class="term-pass">PASS</span>
  <span class="term-pass">&check;</span> <span class="term-gate">gate structure-and-tone</span> <span class="term-pass">PASS</span>

<span class="term-header">&gt;&gt;&gt; Phase "page-tests"</span>
  <span class="term-pass">&check;</span> <span class="term-gate">gate playwright</span>         <span class="term-pass">PASS</span> <span class="term-anno">14 tests &middot; 8.7s</span></pre>

  <div class="meta-suite">
    <div class="meta-cmd">
      <code>site-create-page --set topic="..."</code>
      <span>AI generates a page from repo context, gates verify</span>
    </div>
    <div class="meta-cmd">
      <code>site-update-page --set page=plugins</code>
      <span>AI rewrites a page with your instructions</span>
    </div>
    <div class="meta-cmd">
      <code>site-update</code>
      <span>Regenerate all pages, verify, build</span>
    </div>
    <div class="meta-cmd">
      <code>site-dev</code>
      <span>Dev server with hot reload</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- ── Agent integration ───────────────────── -->
<section id="agents">
<div class="wrap">
  <div class="section-label">integrations</div>
  <h2>Give your agents gl1tch.</h2>

  <div class="agent-cards">
    <div class="agent-card">
      <div class="agent-card-label">Claude Code</div>
      <pre class="code copyable" data-copy="npx @anthropic-ai/superpower install gl1tch"><span class="p">$</span> npx @anthropic-ai/superpower install gl1tch</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="agent-card">
      <div class="agent-card-label">Cursor / Copilot</div>
      <pre class="code copyable" data-copy="curl -sLo .cursorrules https://raw.githubusercontent.com/8op-org/gl1tch/main/skills/cursor/.cursorrules"><span class="p">$</span> curl -sLo .cursorrules <span class="s">https://raw.githubusercontent.com/8op-org/gl1tch/main/skills/cursor/.cursorrules</span></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="agent-card">
      <div class="agent-card-label">Any agent</div>
      <pre class="code copyable" data-copy="curl -sLo AGENTS.md https://raw.githubusercontent.com/8op-org/gl1tch/main/skills/generic/AGENTS.md"><span class="p">$</span> curl -sLo AGENTS.md <span class="s">https://raw.githubusercontent.com/8op-org/gl1tch/main/skills/generic/AGENTS.md</span></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

</main>

</Base>
